#ROOMS
#12170
Name Main Hall~
Desc The main hall of this house is dominated by a large fire pit in the center. 
About 8 feet across and 4 feet deep, this pit can hold the largest of logs 
and a huge amount of coals to warm the coldest of Winter's nights.  It is 
surrounded by several low chairs.  The chairs are made of wood, but they are 
padded and appear quite comfortable.  Many a tale must have been told from 
these seats. The ceiling starts about 8 feet high around the sides of the 
Hall but slopes upwards to a peak about 15 feet high in the center.  The 
ceiling is made of enormously thick, soot-covered beams and opens in a small 
vent that lets smoke out and creates an upwards draft.  Off to the east and 
west sides are two alcoves, well lit and heated by the fire.  The hall 
continues north. 
~
